Reindex requests support a "size" parameter under the "source" parameter, like so:
```
{
  "source": {
    "remote": {
      "host": "http://otherhost:9200",
      "username": "user",
      "password": "pass"
    },
    "index": "source",
    "size": 10
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "dest"
  }
}
```

This affects the batch size that documents from "source" are processed in and is different from the "size" parameter which caps the number of documents that will be reindexed.  Both parameters are included in examples in the [documentation](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/5.0/docs-reindex.html)

